<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 94 / Economic Watch: Italian recovery gathers pace
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Italian economy has begun to move from a timid recovery to sustained
growth. Industrial production figures and the latest official survey of
industrialists' opinion shows the export-led recovery has begun to include a
modest element of renewed domestic demand. According to Istat, the state
statistics institute, industrial production in May was up 7.5 per cent on
the same period the previous year. During the first five months as a whole
industrial production was 2 per cent higher than in 1993. Production of
office equipment was up 14 per cent. Robert Graham, Rome.
In later editions of the FT yesterday, a graph on page 2 mistakenly referred
to Italian bond yields and not, as it should have done, to bond prices.
</TEXT>
