<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 94 / World News in Brief: Sixth rail strike today
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Rail plans to run about 3,800 services today, a quarter of the
normal total, during the sixth 24-hour strike by signal workers. Among
trains running for the first time on a strike day are the King's
Cross-Peterborough, Gillingham-Victoria and Basingstoke-Waterloo services.
