<TEXT>
Sales of PALLADIUM believed to be from Russia - the biggest producer -
capped prices after a rise to fresh five-year highs yesterday afternoon.
Palladium was fixed at Dollars 147.30 a troy ounce, up Dollars 1.05, helping
its sister metal PLATINUM to a three-month high of Dollars 416.75. Dealers
said the early price surge reflected investment fund buying on the New York
futures markets where the rally in the platinum group metals began on
Friday.
GOLD and SILVER silver benefitted from the trend.
