FT  19 JUL 94 / UK Company News: N&amp;P launches home insurance products
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
National &amp; Provincial Building Society yesterday launched a new range of
home insurance products in what could be a prelude to a move into general
insurance under the proposed new powers for societies.
N&amp;P, the UK's eighth-largest society, said it would go into general
insurance if it decided that customers would benefit, for example, through
greater flexibility in products that could be offered.
'The new legislative plans open up quite a big opportunity for building
societies,' said Mr Michael Pendle, N&amp;P's director of general insurance.
He said the new Homechoice range of insurance policies was competitively
priced and offered great flexibility.
Mr David Conway, customer requirements director, said the price
competitiveness had been achieved partly through negotiations with the
insurance companies to reduce the costs of manufacturing the policies, and
partly through N&amp;P cutting its margins 'in some cases very substantially'.
'Building societies have perhaps been too cosy with insurers,' he said.
N&amp;P is initially targeting the new products at its existing 2.8m customers,
savers as well as borrowers.
Some 400,000 to 450,000 customers already have building and contents
insurance with N&amp;P.
