   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shanks &amp; McEwan's former finance director and former chief executive, who
both resigned from the Glasgow-based waste contractor unexpectedly, received
a total of Pounds 761,000 in compensation payments.
The payments cover Mr Roger Hewitt, the chief executive who resigned in
January when the group issued a profits warning, and Mr Alastair Fowler, the
finance director who resigned at the end of September. They are disclosed in
the group's annual report.
The company, which last month cut its dividend by 43 per cent after
announcing a plunge into the red with pre-tax losses of Pounds 6m for the
year to March 26, declined to identify the size of the individual payments.
However, Mr David Downes, who succeeded Mr Fowler as finance director, noted
that both men had three-year employment contracts. All executive directors
are now on two-year contracts.
According to the annual report the compensation payment includes the
estimated Pounds 10,000 value of a car.
